        body: "Touch navigation requires fundamentally different design than mouse-based desktop interaction. Average adult finger pad is 10-14mm wide approximately 38-53 CSS pixels. Google recommends minimum 48x48 CSS pixels tap targets with 8px spacing. When targets are too small or close users experience fat finger errors. Audit all clickable elements: navigation links, buttons, form inputs, accordion toggles, social icons, image links. Check each against 48x48 minimum. In CSS ensure a button min-width 48px min-height 48px. For icon buttons add padding to increase tap area. For navigation increase line-height or padding. Form elements need special attention - radio buttons and checkboxes should have clickable labels wrapping inputs with label tags. Input fields need adequate height min-height 44px. Font sizes: 16px minimum for body text. Google research shows users read more efficiently at 18-20px on mobile. Use CSS clamp for fluid typography: body font-size clamp(16px 4vw 20px). Headings proportionally: h1 font-size clamp(24px 6vw 40px). Line height 1.4-1.6 for mobile readability. Test using Toolverse mobile-friendly test tool and Google Search Console Mobile Usability report."
