        body: "Q1: What is difference between responsive dynamic serving and separate mobile URLs? Responsive design serves same HTML adapts via media queries - Google recommends this. Dynamic serving same URL different HTML based on user-agent. Separate mobile URLs m.example.com need additional configuration. Q2: How often should I run the mobile-friendly test? Test every new page before publishing. Quarterly for existing pages. After any template change test all page types. Monitor GSC Mobile Usability weekly. Q3: Can I have different content on mobile and desktop? Ideally no - mobile-first indexing means mobile version determines rankings. Hiding content in accordion or tabs is fine but removing is problematic. Q4: What about AMP? AMP is no longer required for any Google feature. Standard responsive design optimized for speed is recommended. Q5: Do mobile-friendly fixes improve desktop rankings? Not directly but many fixes better performance cleaner code improved usability benefit overall site quality."
